page.title: 20CARRWOODS
page.content: Carrwoods are across the road from Bramhall Park and right next to the golf club.There is a stream running all through it with a bridge going over it.At one end there is a tunnel that the stream goes through.There are lots of flowers and trees.Some overhang the stream.There are lots of Squirrels to be seen in the Autumn.In the summer families take walks through the wood.Sometimes you find golf balls from the golf club.Children like throwing stones in the stream.There are banks formed from clay,and at the bottom is the stream.We have visited Carrwoods many times with school to study the wildlife,plants and stream. Carrwoods is an extremely good place for bird spotting and for finding rabbits.
